abstract: Bernie Sanders says he raised a whopping $25 million in January and will use his presidential campaign's flush bank account to increase television and digital advertising in 10 states.
snippet: Bernie Sanders says he raised a whopping $25 million in January and will use his presidential campaign's flush bank account to increase television and digital advertising in 10 states.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Bernie Sanders says he raised a whopping $25 million in January and will use his presidential campaign's flush bank account to increase television and digital advertising in 10 states.
headline_main: Sanders Says He Raised $25M in January, Will Bolster Ad Buys
headline_print_headline: Sanders Says He Raised $25M in January, Will Bolster Ad Buys

abstract: The Vermont senator’s announcement came as the Biden, Buttigieg and Warren campaigns are showing signs of financial strain.
snippet: The Vermont senator’s announcement came as the Biden, Buttigieg and Warren campaigns are showing signs of financial strain.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont raised $25 million in January, his campaign said on Thursday, a staggering sum that gives him an enviable financial advantage at a crucial moment in the Democratic primary race.

abstract: You’ve definitively shown us why you shouldn’t be first on the political calendar, and so much more.
snippet: You’ve definitively shown us why you shouldn’t be first on the political calendar, and so much more.
lead_paragraph: As Iowa Democrats struggle to tally votes and claw their way out of the rubble of Monday’s caucus crackup, there continues to be angst and outrage about the damage the Hawkeye State has inflicted on the democratic process — and the Democratic process. Terms like “catastrophe,” “debacle,” “fiasco” and “disaster” are being tossed about like salad greens.

abstract: The approach is not to appear more ethical than the other candidate but to tear down that person’s character.
snippet: The approach is not to appear more ethical than the other candidate but to tear down that person’s character.
lead_paragraph: Given the amount of political news being generated these days, you could be forgiven for not paying close attention to both the Trump-Ukraine scandal and the 2020 presidential campaign. But they are actually one and the same: The scandal is the campaign.

abstract: “Trump is, in effect, a king,” Bee joked on Wednesday. “Not like King Arthur — more like a Burger King.”
